[SN]TITLE[SN]
Sampdoria to wear shirt for earthquake victims

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Sampdoria will wear a special shirt during Saturday's derby with Genoa to mark the victims of the earthquake in central Italy.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
A total of 298 people died during and in the aftermath of the August tragedy.
Sampdoria have already announced that half of the earnings from the game will go to the victims.
"The initiative offering support to the victims of the earthquake is great from the club and its fans," said Sampdoria coach Marco Giampaolo.
The game at the Stadio Luigi Ferraris is the 113th meeting between the Genoese rivals in the Derby della Lanterna.
